hermore, we\nshow that this reduction in conductivity is measured up to ~10 \\mu m away from\na GB. A theoretical model is proposed that captures the local reduction in\nphonon mean-free-paths due to strongly diffuse phonon scattering at the\ndisordered grain boundaries. Our results provide a new framework for\nunderstanding phonon-defect interactions in nanomaterials, with implications\nfor the use of high thermal conductivity polycrystalline materials as heat\nsinks in electronics thermal management.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 11 Apr 2018 18:40:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 29 Jul 2018 23:25:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-07-31"}
