ion about the in-plane component of the sample's\nmagnetization, which is not achievable by standard methods and provides\nadditional information about the stray fields, e.g. as when imaging DWs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 12 Apr 2018 09:49:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-04-13"}
