ities) in networks\nrepresenting different time slices as well as the network of all episodes. Such\nmethods were compared (pairwise and also using various metrics, including\nplausibility). The multilevel method performs reasonably in general. Also, it\nstands out that those methods do not agree very much, resulting in groups that\nare very different from method to method.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 12 Apr 2018 10:15:48 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 5 Oct 2018 09:20:38 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 11 Dec 2019 13:03:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-06-09"}
